; ANSYS Fluent journal sketch for the F-22 external-flow case.
; This repository viewer consumes exported result_mesh.json, not native Fluent
; post files. Run a real Fluent solve with a watertight aircraft mesh, then
; export pressure/Mach/wake slices into the same JSON schema.

/file/set-tui-version "26.1"
/define/models/solver/density-based-implicit yes
/define/models/energy yes
/define/models/viscous/kw-sst yes
/define/materials/change-create air air yes ideal-gas yes constant 1006.43 constant 0.0242 constant 1.46e-05
; Import mesh:
; /file/read-mesh "F22_ExternalFlow.msh.h5"
; Boundary condition intent:
; velocity inlet: Mach 0.85, 3 deg angle of attack at 10 km standard-atmosphere density
; pressure farfield/outlet: 10 km ambient pressure and temperature
; aircraft wall: no-slip adiabatic wall
; convergence target: residuals 1e-5 plus stable CL/CD over at least 500 iterations
; postprocess: export aircraft Cp, midplane pressure/Mach slice, wake slice, and vortex indicators
